<L>__{exterior courthouse peter fallow late afternoon}
<A>__{is sitting on the steps of the courthouse. he is still covered with mud from having been trampled earlier. he takes a long swig from a bottle wrapped in a paper bag. he is drunk.}
<C>__{peter }
<D>__{it was too much for me. all of it. sherman mccoy had been swept away from me. before i could even speak to him. and as the day progressed, i began to appreciate the power, the magnitude of the force that had been unleashed by my little story.}
<A>__{angle moving crowd of reporters, television people, photographers, etc. they run up the steps past peter as they head toward the entrance to the courthouse. as they pass...}
<C>__{voices}
<D>__{it's over! he's coming out! let's go! let's go!}
<A>__{angle peter dodges the onslaught, pulls himself up, and starts moving in the opposite direction.}
<C>__{peter }
<D>__{jackels. dogs. yapping at the heels of their prey. and i was one of them. well, let them have it. enough is enough. i was finished. i summoned what little dignity i had left and decided to go home...}
<C>__{sherman }
<D>__{excuse me, do you know where i can find a taxi?}
<B>__{angle to include sherman mccoy}
<A>__{who has just come out the side entrance of the building. peter is flabbergasted.}
<C>__{peter}
<D>__{jesus christ.}
<C>__{sherman}
<D>__{sherman mccoy.}
<C>__{peter}
<D>__{yes. i know. i know that. what are you...?}
<C>__{sherman}
<D>__{i need a taxi.}
<C>__{peter}
<D>__{you need to get out of here.}
<A>__{angle crowd of reporters change direction and start moving away from the front entrance and toward the side entrance. as they go...}
<C>__{voices}
<D>__{the other way! other way! he's coming out the back! move! move! move!}
<A>__{angle fallow and sherman see the mob moving toward them. fallow grabs sherman and pulls him toward a subway.}
<C>__{peter}
<D>__{this way. come on.}
<C>__{sherman}
<D>__{uh. i don't normally ride the subway.}
<C>__{peter}
<D>__{me either. especially on a first date. but we don't really have a choice.}
